New task: Fix `read_messages` in `src/mcp-server.ts` to include the message ID in each formatted message.

**Problem:** The `read_messages` handler formats messages but omits `m.id`. Agents have no way to extract the message ID and cannot pass a correct `source_msg_id` to `delegate_task`.

**Location:** `src/mcp-server.ts` around line 388–397 (the `read_messages` handler):

```ts
const formatted = msgs
  .map((m) => {
    const ts = new Date(m.created_at).toISOString();
    const label = m.priority === 0 ? '[P0 — URGENT]' : '[P5]';
    return `${label} From: ${m.from_id} at ${ts}\n${m.content}`;
  })
  .join('\n\n---\n\n');
```

**Fix:** Add `[id=${m.id}]` to the label line:

```ts
return `${label} [id=${m.id}] From: ${m.from_id} at ${ts}\n${m.content}`;
```

The `Message` interface in `src/db.ts` already exposes `id: number` — no type changes needed.

Also update the `source_msg_id` parameter description for `delegate_task` in `src/mcp-server.ts` (around line 341) to say: "get the ID from the `[id=N]` tag in the `read_messages` output".

**Deliverable:** Edit `src/mcp-server.ts` only. `npm run build` must pass. Commit when done. Report DONE to cec50b17:0.

